╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║          SSH Test Server - Dropbear/BusyBox Edition           ║
║                   SCP Only - No SFTP                          ║
╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

Welcome to the SSH Test Server (Dropbear on Alpine Linux)
Simulates BusyBox/embedded devices with SSH + SCP but NO SFTP

📋 Available Tools:
  • dropbear    - Dropbear SSH server
  • dbclient    - Dropbear SSH client
  • scp         - Secure copy (SCP protocol)

⚠️  Deliberately Excluded:
  • sftp        - NOT INSTALLED (simulates BusyBox devices)
  • sftp-server - NOT INSTALLED

ℹ️  System Information:
  • Base: Alpine Linux 3.19 + Dropbear
  • SSH Port: ${SSH_PORT}
  • User: ${SSH_USER}
  • Debug Level: ${SSH_DEBUG_LEVEL}

🔧 Configuration:
  • Password Auth: ${SSH_PERMIT_PASSWORD_AUTH}
  • Public Key Auth: always enabled (Dropbear default)
  • SCP: ENABLED
  • SFTP: DISABLED

💡 Quick Tips:
  • Use 'scp -O' for legacy SCP protocol transfers
  • SFTP connections will fail with "subsystem request failed"
  • Logs available via 'docker logs' command
  • Reference: https://github.com/billchurch/webssh2/issues/483

